hentry","category-righteousness-al-birr","tag-forbearance-al-hilm","tag-forgiveness-al-maghfirah","tag-good-deeds-hasanat","tag-legal-punishment-al-hudud","tag-manhood-al-muruah","tag-manners-adab","tag-pardon-al-afwa","tag-patience-sabr","tag-punishment-al-uqubah","tag-virtue-al-fadail"],"aioseo_notices":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"","jetpack_shortlink":"https:\/\/wp.me\/p95VHY-5P8","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack-related-posts":[{"id":25273,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/10\/11\/hudud-pardon-faults-not-crimes\/","url_meta":{"origin":22390,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Hudud: Pardon good people their faults, not crimes","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 11, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cOverlook the faults of good people, except for legal punishments.\u201d Source: Sunan Abi\u0304 Da\u0304wu\u0304d 4375 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0627\u0626\u0650\u0634\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0636\u0650\u064a\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0647\u064e\u0627 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e\u062a\u0652 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0642\u0650\u064a\u0644\u064f\u0648\u0627 \u0630\u064e\u0648\u0650\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0647\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0626\u064e\u0627\u062a\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":19388,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/06\/21\/pardon-hudud-if-possible\/","url_meta":{"origin":22390,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Hudud: Pardon criminal before notifying ruler, if possible","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 21, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Amr reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cPardon the legal punishments between yourselves, for whatever offense reaches me must be punished.\u201d Source: Sunan Abi\u0304 Da\u0304wu\u0304d 4376 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0645\u0652\u0631\u0650\u0648 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0639\u064e\u0627\u0635\u0650 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0651\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":21332,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2015\/12\/16\/umar-hudud-punish-doubts\/","url_meta":{"origin":22390,"position":2},"title":"Umar on Hudud: Better to pardon than punish with doubts","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 16, 2015","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibrahim al-Nakha\u2019i reported: Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cThat I relax the legal punishments is more beloved to me than applying them with doubts.\u201d Source: Mus\u0323annaf Ibn Abi\u0304 Shaybah 27926 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Sakhawi \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0625\u0628\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0627\u0647\u0650\u064a\u0645\u064e \u